<subsection xml:id="subsec-Angles-in-a-straightline">
<title>Angles in a straight line</title> 
    <activity>
    
        <p>
            <term><em>What you need: a ruler and a protractor</em></term>
            
        </p>

        <image width="50%">
            <shortdescription>line</shortdescription>
            <latex-image label="straight-line">
            \begin{tikzpicture}
                \draw(-1,0) node[left]{$A$} -- (1,0) node[right]{$B$};
                \draw(0,-.1) -- (0,.1) node[below]{$O$};
            \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
                            
        </image>
    
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        
                        Draw a straight line <m>AB</m> and mark point <m>O</m> at the centre as shown above.    
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Draw two lines to make an angle with line <m>AB</m> at point <m>O</m> as shown in the diagram below.
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                
                                Measure the angles you have drawn.
                    
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                How do the angles relate to each other?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
            
            <image width="50%">
                <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                <latex-image>
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        \draw[blue](-1,0) coordinate(A) -- (0,0) coordinate(O) -- (1,0) coordinate(B);
                        \draw[blue](-.7,1) coordinate(C) -- (0,0) coordinate(O) -- (.7,1) coordinate(D);
                        \draw(-1,-.1) node[left]{$A$};
                        \draw(0,-.1) node{$O$};
                        \draw(1,-.1) node[right]{$B$};
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                
            </image>

            <p>
                <term><em>Learning point</em></term>
                    
            </p>

            <p>
                Angles on a straight line always add up to <m>180^\circ</m>. 
                This is because a straight line itself is considered a "straight angle" which measures exactly <m>180^\circ</m>. 

            </p>

            <p>
                Any <em>two</em> angles that add up to <m>180^\circ</m> are <em>supplementary angles.</em>
            </p>
        
    </activity>

    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
            Calculate the size of the angle labeled <m>k</m> in the figure below.
            </p> 
                <image width="50%">
                    <shortdescription> Angles on a straight line.</shortdescription>
                        <latex-image>
                            \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \usetikzlibrary{quotes,angles}
                                    \draw(-4,0) --(4,0);
                                    \draw (-4,0) coordinate (A)-- (4,0) coordinate (C);
                                    \draw(-3,5) coordinate (E)-- (0,0) coordinate (B)-- (3,4) coordinate (D);
                                    <!-- \node at(-4.2,0){A};
                                    \node at (0,-0.2){B};
                                    \node at (4.2,0){C};
                                    \node at(3.2,4.2){D};
                                    \node at (-3.2,5.1){E}; -->
                                    \pic["$50$", draw,-&gt;,black, angle radius=1cm] {angle=C--B--D};
                                    \pic["$k$", draw,-&gt;,black, angle radius=0.8cm] {angle=D--B--E};
                                    \pic["$55$", draw,-&gt;,black, angle radius=1cm] {angle=E--B--A};
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                        </latex-image>
                </image>
        </statement>
        
        <solution>
            <p>
                Angles on a straight line add upto <m>180^\circ</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                The angle <m>k</m> can be solved by adding <m>55^\circ+k+50^\circ</m>;
            </p>
            <p>
                Equating <me>55^\circ +k + 50^\circ =1 80^\circ</me>,we get;
            </p>
            <p>
                <me>
                k=180^\circ-105^\circ
                </me> 
            </p>
            <p>
                <me>
                \text{Therefore}, k = 75^\circ
                </me>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </activity>


